{
    "transcription_text": "ESG is a term that's become increasingly widespread over the past few years. But with the many different interpretations surrounding it, what does ESG integration mean? Simply put, it's the consideration of environmental, social, and governance factors into investment analysis to identify material risks and opportunities. As a strategic advisor and long-term partner to our clients, we integrate the analysis of ESG topics into the investment process across all asset classes. Baring's teams use many levers at hand across ESG integration and stewardship to help us identify investment opportunities while also delivering on our commitment as a corporate citizen. That's because, in our experience, considering ESG factors in our fundamental, bottom-up analysis leads to better understanding of relevant ESG risks, unlocks ESG opportunities, and is key to evaluating risk-adjusted returns for our clients.",
